[3]
Date: Thu 22 Aug 2019
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2019 [edited]
https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=31517


Anthrax, Armenia
-----------------
Information received on [and dated] 22 Aug 2019 from Dr Georgi Avetisyan, head, Food Safety Inspection Body of the Government of the Republic of Armenia, e ARM Ministry of Agriculture of the Republic of Armenia, Yerevan, Armenia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 19 Aug 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 21 Aug 2019
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak cluster 1: Geghovit, Martuni, Gegharkounik (1 outbreak)
Date of start of the outbreak: 19 Aug 2019
Outbreak status: resolved (21 Aug 2019)
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 3 / 1 / 0 / 1 / 0
Affected population: village with 3450 cattle and 1832 sheep/goats. All animals had been vaccinated except the diseased animal.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 33 / 0 / 0 / 33
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: pasture ground
Epidemiological comments: The animal became infected in the pasture, from the ground. There were no other sick animals.

Control measures
Measures applied: surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, selective killing and disposal, no treatment of affected animals, vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):
Administrative division / Species / Total vaccinated / Details
Gegharkounik / cattle / 3449 / -
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Republican Veterinary-Sanitary and Phytosanitary Laboratory Services Center (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / Ascoli test / 22 Aug 2019 / positive
Cattle / bacteriological examination / 21 Aug 2019 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

